subsection.header:
Risk-based
				performance standards; vulnerability assessments; site security plans;
				emergency response plans

subparagraph.text:
establishing
				risk-based performance standards for the security of covered water systems;
				and

clause.text:
to develop,
				implement, and, as appropriate, revise a site security plan not less than every
				5 years and promptly after a revision to the vulnerability assessment;

subparagraph.text:
establishment of
				risk-based tiers and process for the assignment of covered water systems to
				risk-based tiers;

process for the
				development and evaluation of vulnerability assessments, site security plans,
				and emergency response plans;

substantially
				disrupt the ability of the system to provide a safe and reliable supply of
				drinking water;

paragraph.text:
electronic,
				computer, and other automated systems that are used by the covered water
				system;

clause.text:
an
				intentional act to cause a release, including a worst-case release, of a
				substance of concern at the covered water system;

subparagraph.text:
the modification
				of pressures, temperatures, or concentrations of a substance of concern;
				and

a description of
				the methods to reduce the consequences of a chemical release from an
				intentional act;

clause.text:
would not
				increase the interim storage of a substance of concern by the covered water
				system;

would be
				detrimental to the security of one or more covered water systems if disclosed;
				and

information that
				is otherwise publicly available, including information that is required to be
				made publicly available under any law;

the number of
				public water systems that provided the Administrator with information pursuant
				to subsection (d)(1);

the number of
				vulnerability assessments and site security plans submitted by covered water
				systems;

the number of
				vulnerability assessments and site security plans approved and disapproved by
				the Administrator;

the number of
				covered water systems without approved vulnerability assessments or site
				security plans;

the number of
				audits and inspections conducted by the Administrator or duly designated
				representatives of the Administrator;

the
				administrative penalties assessed by the Administrator for non-compliance with
				the requirements of this section;

subparagraph.text:
preparing and
				updating vulnerability assessments, site security plans, and emergency response
				plans;
